HEADWORD: Neuropteris
<hw>Neu*rop"te*ris</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>ney^ron</grk> a nerve + <?/ a kind of fern.]</ety>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An extensive genus of fossil ferns, of which
species have been found from the Devonian to the Triassic
formation.</def>⟦br⟧
